'.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH KAFS 1 "2026-03-15" "kafs 0.3.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kafs \- FUSE-based KAFS filesystem
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kafs
.RB [ --image
.IR image ]
.I mountpoint
.RI [ FUSE\ options ]
.PP
.B kafs
.RB [ --image
.IR image ]
.B --migrate
.RB [ --yes ]
.I mountpoint
.RI [ FUSE\ options ]
.PP
.B kafs
.I image
.I mountpoint
.RI [ FUSE\ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kafs
mounts a KAFS filesystem image via FUSE.
An embedded journal region is used when present. Sidecar journals are not supported.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Global Options
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.BR --image " " <image>
Specify image path.
.TP
.BR --image= " <image>
Specify image path (inline form).
.TP
.BR --option " " <opt[,opt...]>
Alias for FUSE
.BR -o .
Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
.BR --option= " <opt[,opt...]>
Inline form of
.BR --option .
.TP
.B --migrate
If the image format is v2 or v3, perform offline pre-start migration to v4 and exit.
This operation is irreversible.
.TP
.B --migrate-v2
Deprecated alias of
.BR --migrate .
.TP
.B --yes
Skip interactive confirmation for migration.
.SS Cache And TRIM
.TP
.BR --writeback-cache
Enable writeback cache.
.TP
.BR --no-writeback-cache
Disable writeback cache.
.TP
.BR --trim-on-free
Enable TRIM (hole punch) when data blocks become free.
.TP
.BR --no-trim-on-free
Disable TRIM when data blocks become free.
.TP
.BR -o " " writeback_cache
Enable writeback cache via FUSE 
.B -o
.
.TP
.BR -o " " no_writeback_cache
Disable writeback cache via FUSE 
.B -o
.
.TP
.BR -o " " trim_on_free " | " trim-on-free
Enable runtime TRIM via FUSE 
.B -o
.
.TP
.BR -o " " no_trim_on_free " | " no-trim-on-free
Disable runtime TRIM via FUSE 
.B -o
.
.SS Threading And Worker Tuning
.TP
.BR "-o multi_thread" "[=N]"
Enable FUSE multi-thread mode and set worker thread count.
This is translated to FUSE option
.BR max_threads= .
Aliases:
.BR multi-thread
and
.BR multithread .
.TP
.BR -o " " pending_worker_prio= "<normal|idle>"
Set pending worker scheduling mode.
.TP
.BR -o " " pending_worker_nice= "<0..19>"
Set pending worker nice value.
.TP
.BR -o " " dedup_worker_prio= "<normal|idle>"
Alias for
.BR pending_worker_prio .
.TP
.BR -o " " dedup_worker_nice= "<0..19>"
Alias for
.BR pending_worker_nice .
.TP
.BR -o " " bg_dedup_scan= "<on|off>"
Enable or disable idle background dedup scan.
Default is
.BR on .
.TP
.BR -o " " dedup_scan= "<on|off>"
Alias for
.BR bg_dedup_scan .
.TP
.BR -o " " bg_dedup_interval_ms= "<N>"
Set idle background dedup scan interval in milliseconds.
.TP
.BR -o " " dedup_interval_ms= "<N>"
Alias for
.BR bg_dedup_interval_ms .
.SS Hotplug
.TP
.B --hotplug
Enable hotplug bootstrap using the default UDS endpoint
.IR /tmp/kafs-hotplug.sock .
.TP
.BR --hotplug= " <uds>"
Enable hotplug bootstrap and set the UDS endpoint path.
.TP
.BR --hotplug-uds " " <uds>
Set the hotplug bootstrap UDS endpoint path.
.TP
.BR --hotplug-back-bin " " <path>
Set backend binary path hint stored in hotplug env
.RB ( KAFS_HOTPLUG_BACK_BIN ).
.TP
.BR -o " " hotplug "[=" "<uds>" "]"
Alias for
.BR --hotplug .
When
.I <uds>
is specified, it is equivalent to
.BR --hotplug= .
.PP
The current implementation retains UDS for initial bootstrap and relisten compatibility.
Subsequent
.B kafsctl hotplug restart-back
operations use the supervised restart path managed by the mounted front process.
.TP
.BR -o " " hotplug_uds= "<uds>"
Alias for
.BR --hotplug-uds .
.TP
.BR -o " " hotplug_back_bin= "<path>"
Alias for
.BR --hotplug-back-bin .
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KAFS_IMAGE
Fallback path to image when --image is not specified.
.TP
.B KAFS_WRITEBACK_CACHE
Default writeback cache mode (1: enabled, 0: disabled).
.TP
.B KAFS_TRIM_ON_FREE
Default TRIM-on-free mode (1: enabled, 0: disabled).
.TP
.B KAFS_JOURNAL
Set to 0 to disable journal even if present.
.TP
.B KAFS_MT
Set to 1 to enable FUSE multi-thread mode (same effect as
.BR "-o multi_thread" ).
.TP
.B KAFS_MAX_THREADS
Default thread count used when multi-thread mode is enabled and N is not specified.
.TP
.B KAFS_PENDING_WORKER_PRIO
Default value for
.BR -o " " pending_worker_prio= .
.TP
.B KAFS_PENDING_WORKER_NICE
Default value for
.BR -o " " pending_worker_nice= .
.TP
.B KAFS_BG_DEDUP_SCAN
Default on/off switch for idle background dedup scan (default: on).
.TP
.B KAFS_BG_DEDUP_INTERVAL_MS
Default scan interval in milliseconds for idle background dedup.
.TP
.B KAFS_HOTPLUG_UDS
Hotplug bootstrap UDS endpoint path used when explicit hotplug options are not provided.
.TP
.B KAFS_HOTPLUG_BACK_BIN
Backend binary path hint exposed via hotplug env list.
.TP
.B KAFS_JOURNAL_GC_NS
Group commit window in nanoseconds (default 10000000ns).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mkfs.kafs (8),
.BR fsck.kafs (8),
.BR kafsctl (1),
.BR kafsdump (8),
.BR kafsimage (8),
.BR kafsresize (8),
.BR kafs-info (8),
.BR kafs-front (8),
.BR kafs-back (8)
.SH AUTHOR
kafs project.
